The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Oyo State has advised Governor Seyi Makinde to lockdown the state to trace the victims of the coronavirus pandemic in the state. The party also urged the Makinde to explore more proactive measures to curb the spread of the virus in the state. The party in a statement by its Publicity Secretary, Dr. AbdulAzeez Olatunde, said that contact tracing would be easier once a ban was placed on movements. Ajimobi, APC congratulate Oyo governor-elect Makinde Appeal Court judgement: Oyo people’s mandate remains intact – Makinde Ajimobi, APC congratulate Makinde, thank Oyo voters